content: The link you are trying to open does not exist.

comment.text: This translation key is used to display a message when a link does not exist. It is typically shown as an error message in UI components, such as an alert or dialog box, after attempting to access a non-existent link.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While technically correct, the translation 'Açmağa çalışdığınız keçid mövcud deyil' is a bit formal for a user-facing error message. A more natural and user-friendly phrasing would be preferable.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a more conversational alternative like 'Daxil etdiyiniz keçid tapılmadı.' or 'Sizə göstərilən keçid işləmir.'

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao translation 'ບໍ່ມີລິ້ງທີ່ເຈົ້າພະຍາຍາມເປີດ' is a literal translation that doesn't quite capture the natural flow of the English phrase 'The link you are trying to open does not exist.' A more natural translation would emphasize that the link is broken or invalid.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ບໍ່ສາມາດເປີດລິ້ງນີ້ໄດ້ ຫຼື ບໍ່ມີຢູ່ແລ້ວ (Bakam san pert ling ni dai rue bor mi yu laeo) - This translates to 'This link cannot be opened or does not exist.'

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While technically correct, using 'ບໍສາມາດ' (bakam san) instead of 'ບໍ່ມີ' (bor mi) offers a more appropriate tone and clarity for a technical error message.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Replace 'ບໍ່ມີ' with 'ບໍສາມາດ'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'Link' is not accurately translated. 'Link' refers to a hyperlink.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Legătura pe care încercați să o deschideți nu există.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "Ссылки, которую вы пытаетесь открыть, не существует." is a literal translation that sounds slightly awkward in Russian. A more natural phrasing would be something like "Указанная ссылка не существует" or "Ссылка, которую вы пытаетесь открыть, не найдена."
